# Master Data Sets

- One master data set for each main level of observation in your data set
- Create a list of all observations ever encountered -- even if they are not in the analysis sample
- The Master Data Set is the authoritative source for all IDs and identifying information

# Data Flowchart

- Creates an overview of key steps for processing data, creating a model for your data work and a shared understanding within the team of what needs to be done and in which order
- Lists all the data tables needed for analysis, all the raw data tables, and indicate how to create one from the other 
- Include in the flowchart the main steps for data processing, and take note of more complex and error-prone tasks

